Ad Text:
12 + 6 + 6month contract - July Start
NV1 Security Clearance required
50% WFH / 50% work from QLD, WA, ACT, VIC, NSW, NT, SA, TAS 
EL1 equivalent | Azure Data | ETL Development | Power BI

Our client, a Federal Government department that promotes competition and fair trade to benefit consumers, businesses, and the wider community, is seeking an experienced Senior Data Developer.

Duties of the Senior Data Developer

Contribute to technical design and development on one or more projects within the programs;
Design and develop data workflows, ETL processes, data warehouse, data lake, data analytics and data visualisation solutions;
Advise on improvements to processes, products and deployed code;
Lead technical design and development of projects;
Design and develop data workflows, ETL processes, and end-to-end data solutions including data warehouses, data lakes, databases, and visualisation tools.

Skills and Experience Required

At least 3+ years of experience in Data Development;
Experience in detailed design for data integration on Azure cloud data services including ADLS, SQL DB, data lake Synapse and blob storage;
Proficient with Azure Data Factory and Azure Event Hub;
Development experience with Power BI (stored procedure, DAX, functions, views);
Knowledge of government regulations, policies, and ethical considerations surrounding AI/ML technologies and data sources.

How to Apply
For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions please get in touch with Jess P at the Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively, you can reach Jess P on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further.

Please note, applications close on Thursday, 30 April 2026 at midday, Canberra time.

